Product definition
- PRD Skill
- User Story Mapper (How things actually look - flows and such

High level design
- Architecture Skill

Designers
- Frontend designer skill (logic, state, UI/UX direction, stack selection)
- Backend designer skill (API + core logic, language/framework selection)
- Database designer skill (SQL/NoSQL selection, schema design)
- Agentic system designer skill (orchestration, memory/RAG, tools/MCP, prompts)
- Security designer skill
- Design synchronizer skill (conflict detection + zero-conflicts pass)

Recommended run order
- Architecture Skill
- Backend designer skill
- Database designer skill
- Frontend designer skill
- Agentic system designer skill
- Security designer skill
- Design synchronizer skill

Planning
- Task Planner Skill (Parallel / Sequential, multiple instances)

Implementing
- Backend implementation skill (Logic, API framework and implementation, schemas and data validation, security
- Agentic implementation skill
- Complete backend implementation synchronizer skill
- Frontend Coding Skill (Implements UI and client logic, Integrates with backend APIs

After coding
- Evaluation & Feedback Skill (Reviews agent outputs, Detects failures, Triggers retries or human review)
- Security Review Skill (Advises on auth, secrets, permissions)
- Testing Skill (UT, Validates correctness against PRD)
- Linting & Code Quality Skill (Flake8, Enforces style)
- Documentation Skill (In the code base, Developer/User docs, Keeps sync with implementation)
- CI/CD Skill
- DevOps Skill (Hosting strategy, Plans environments (dev / staging / prod)
